        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Blasts of fire and smoke pour out of the tunnel walls to coalesce into the burning form of Dahak himself; a PC who succeeds at a @Check[type:religion|dc:20|name:Recognize Depiction of Dahak|traits:hazard,complex,fire,magical,trap,action:recall-knowledge] check to Recall Knowledge notes that the fiery dragon closely resembles classical depictions of the draconic god of destruction.</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[type:religion|dc:26|name:Counteract Dahak With Prayers|traits:complex,fire,magical,trap,hazard] (expert) to utter prayers to a non-evil deity to counteract Dahak's presence (prayers to Apsu allow this check to be made if the character is merely trained in Religion), @Check[type:thievery|dc:30|name:Divert the Hazard's Energy Back|traits:complex,fire,magical,trap,hazard] (expert) to divert the hazard's energies back upon themselves, or a successful <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Dispel Magic]{Dispel Magic}</em> (4th level; counteract DC 26).</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 8
            },
            "reset": "<p>The vision of Dahak deactivates and resets automatically once no creatures remain within the Huntergate way station.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(2 actions) The vision of Dahak manifests next to the creature that is closest to the center of the way station, then uses its Breath Weapon in a direction that catches the most possible targets in its area.</p>"
        },
